{"id": "EUVD-2024-3330", "enisaUuid": "cbf0fd13-447d-3de3-abfe-c2d83e43e8ca", "description": "symfony/runtime is a module for the Symphony PHP framework which enables decoupling PHP applications from global state. When the `register_argv_argc` php directive is set to `on` , and users call any URL with a special crafted query string, they are able to change the environment or debug mode used by the kernel when handling the request. As of versions 5.4.46, 6.4.14, and 7.1.7 the `SymfonyRuntime` now ignores the `argv` values for non-SAPI PHP runtimes. All users are advised to upgrade. There are no known workarounds for this vulnerability.", "datePublished": "2024-11-06T21:09:46", "dateUpdated": "2024-11-07T15:29:50", "baseScore": 7.3, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L", "references": ["https://github.com/symfony/symfony/security/advisories/GHSA-x8vp-gf4q-mw5j", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-50340", "https://github.com/symfony/symfony/commit/a77b308c3f179ed7c8a8bc295f82b2d6ee3493fa", "https://github.com/FriendsOfPHP/security-advisories/blob/master/symfony/runtime/CVE-2024-50340.yaml", "https://github.com/FriendsOfPHP/security-advisories/blob/master/symfony/symfony/CVE-2024-50340.yaml", "https://github.com/symfony/symfony", "https://symfony.com/cve-2024-50340"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-50340", "GHSA-x8vp-gf4q-mw5j"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 87.26, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0ac4c9de-2ccc-32a9-bdef-88ad5ffca908", "product": {"name": "symfony"}, "product_version": "< 5.4.46"}, {"id": "660d352e-4da1-3e80-a24a-d5cbba79cb5c", "product": {"name": "symfony"}, "product_version": "6.0.0, < 6.4.14"}, {"id": "9ebeb078-6f68-3224-b82b-54d9880d31e1", "product": {"name": "symfony"}, "product_version": "7.0.0, < 7.1.7"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "8fe23122-c710-3b45-9220-7e5b97875bf2", "vendor": {"name": "symfony"}}], "isExploited": false}